      "text": [
        " قَالَ عَلِيُّ بْنُ أَبِي طَالِبٍ صَلوَاتُ اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ : «لاَ تَقُولُوا رَمَضَانُ وَ لَكِنْ قُولُوا« شَهْرُ رَمَضٰانَ » فَإِنَّكُمْ لاَ تَدْرُونَ مَا رَمَضَانُ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2051 - It is narrated from Ghiyath ibn Ibrahim, from Abu Abdullah (as), from his father (as), from his grandfather (as), who said that Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as) said:\n\"Do not say 'Ramadan'; rather, say 'the Month of Ramadan,' for you do not know what 'Ramadan' is.\""
        ]
      }
    },
